originalText.text: I went there May 12, 2022 from out of state and decided to go inside the parking garage since the price posted said $12 with few cents. I enter the garage and I ask the two workers to make sure of the price and they looked at me and said $15. I reply and said why since the advertised priced said $12 with few cents. I keep going back and forward with them, because I didn't understand why is $15. Both workers gave me an attitude and I left very disappointed with there professionalism overall and especially for not explaining how it jump from $12 to so much $15. When I went to Icon parking garage around the corner, they explaining with a professional way that the difference is the tax is so much. Now I got it clear why it jump so much, since the taxes are so high. Definitely, the workers in this garage Hampton Court can't or don't want to explain anything and just want you to paid like if you were rich. Very disappointed with their professionalism, like if I have read their mind on what they mean.
